    <thetext>Current checks on &apos;this===undefined&apos; in test262 strict mode tests seems to mostly revolve around either Function.prototype.call(undefined)/Function.prototype.apply calls or strict mode at the global level.  We also need to make sure scenarios such as:
   (function (){&quot;use strict&quot;; return this===undefined;}();
are adequately covered.  Specifically, we should look into mutating cases found under 10.4.3 and 11.1.1.</thetext>
